<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="486" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="486">
Two subspecies of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1858" box="[1039,1184,2729,2758]" class="Mammalia" family="Phalangeridae" genus="Strigocuscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diprotodontia" pageId="5" pageNumber="486" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="celebensis">S. celebensis</taxonomicName>
are often recognized, but a more detailed assessment of geographical and elevational variation in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1861" box="[827,980,2842,2875]" class="Mammalia" family="Phalangeridae" genus="Strigocuscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diprotodontia" pageId="5" pageNumber="486" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Strigocuscus</taxonomicName>
across Sulawesi is needed. As currently recognized, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1858" box="[1141,1290,2881,2914]" class="Mammalia" family="Phalangeridae" genus="Strigocuscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diprotodontia" pageId="5" pageNumber="486" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="celebensis">S. celebensis</taxonomicName>
prob¿DW represents more than one species. Two subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
